'''Omi (Omi/Momi) clan''' (小見, 麻績) is one of the clans of Japan.
== Hei Clan Omi == The Omi clan ('''Komi clan''') originating from {{ill|Omi-go, Katori District|ja|小見郷|12=draft}} in {{ill|Shimōsa Province|ja|下総国|12=draft}} (present-day {{ill|Katori, Chiba|ja|香取市|12=draft}}, Chiba Prefecture) belonged to the {{ill|Bōsō Taira|ja|房総平氏|12=draft}} lineage. Several branches emerged: * The {{ill|Sōsa Party Omi|ja|匝瑳氏|12=draft}} clan, stemming from the {{ill|Kazusa clan|ja|上総氏|12=draft}}. * The lineage of {{ill|Chiba Tsunetane|ja|千葉常胤|12=draft}}’s younger brother {{ill|Omi Tanechika|ja|小見胤隆|12=draft}}. * The lineage of {{ill|Shiina Tademitsu|ja|椎名胤光|12=draft}}’s son {{ill|Omi Tanesumi|ja|小見胤澄|12=draft}}. * The lineage of {{ill|Higashi Tadakazu|ja|東胤頼|12=draft}}’s grandson {{ill|Omi Tanechika|ja|小見胤直|12=draft}}.
